content.detailedDescription:
I was going to the grocery store in cazenovia, ny. at approximately 6:20 i turned right onto stone quarry rd from hardscrabble rd and noticed what i thought was a very low-flying airplane. i could clearly see two white lights at the ends of a linear object with a red light in the center. the white lights flashed on and off together; the red light was steady. i could see that this was a large object and close to the ground... considerably above trees but below clouds. it proceeded northeast, as did i. i turned left and lost sight of it, but when i made the next right (maybe a quarter mile) the object was no longer in view. 

i grew up near an airport, so when i see lights in the sky, i don't automatically assume anything unusual is going on. it was on my way home from the store about 6:50 that i realized i'd never seen that light pattern before. when i got home, i did an internet search for aircraft with that light pattern and couldn't find anything. that's when i began to wonder what i'd seen.

limited internet image searches didn't produce any results for aircraft or standard ufos. i see that three white lights with one central red one are fairly common for ufos and because of my viewing angle i can't rule out the possibility of a third white light.

i wasn't frightened, nothing malfunctioned and the only reason it caught my attention was because where i live is ~40 miles from hancock international and the object appeared way too low and slow to be heading there, and it was going in the wrong direction for an emergency landing at the small hamilton airport. it wasn't until later that i realized it wasn't making a jet sound (and i did not have the radio on). a large airplane that near would surely have been audible.

i don't insist that this was a sighting of an extraterrestrial craft - i'm just curious as to what it was that i saw.

i didn't have my phone with me, but i'm not sure it would have occurred to me to take a photo anyway.
content.summary: Linear object - white lights at either end that flashed together, steady red light in the center, flying slow, low, silent

content.detailedDescription:
On february 24, 2016, i was driving to work and took 169n.  at approximately a 1/4 mile south of 394 at 5:55 am, a flicker to my left caught my eye and i looked up and saw a red glowing orb the color of a stoplight and it was blinking at a steady rate.  i'm not absolutely positive, but i think it had an unlighted narrow, black band around its equator region. it was still dark outside and i'm not good at judging distances but it seemed like it was a few yards above the tree tops. i watched it travel on a straight path as it crossed the highway heading east and i watched it fly in an arc then descend as if it was going to land and that's when i lost sight of it. again, i'm not good at judging distances, but i think it was less than a mile east of 169n when it descended.  when it was over the highway, it was about the size of a dime held at arms length; if it was bigger it wasn't by much.  i remember saying to myself it was small.

i wondered when i first saw it if it was a plane, helicopter or drone.  i was very calm and not very excited about seeing it, thinking a person had to be involved with this.  later i thought it was no way a plane or helicopter because it was too low, at least for a plane.  and even though it was still dark out, there was enough ambient light i think i would have been able to discern the body of a plane or helicopter at that height.  i couldn't hear anything accept the road noise from my car.

i am acquainted with the minnesota mufon state director and contacted him to discuss what i saw. after he heard my account, he said it was a typical sighting.  i got more thrilled about the object after that.
content.summary: I saw a red flashing orb w/a black equator-like band above 169n & watched it travel east & descend. i did not actually see if it landed or not. i was driving my car to work & saw it at 5:55 am

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my bedroom late at night, playing on my phone because i couldn't sleep. at the time i lived in a very rural area, woods surrounded my house on all sides and i rarely ever saw airplanes or helicopters through my smallish bedroom window. that night, which was about half a year ago, i was wide awake. completely absorbed in whatever game i had been playing. out of the corner of my eye i saw a bright light flash in the sky and i looked out, confused. it was a bright, glowing, orb-shaped object high in the sky and probably very far away since i couldn't pick out any sort of details. right away i thought it was something otherworldly seeing as nothing man made could've done what i saw it do. it moved in a slow zigzag pattern left to right and down, then it curved back up and hovered. it was very bright seeing as it was so far away and i was viewing it through the trees and it cast the trees' shadow into my room. it was the color of an old streetlight, orangish but sort of white. about two minutes into watching it hover it started to move again in a j shape, then it slowly moved to the west and out of my window's view. i had a strange feeling, i was only mildly curious as to what it was though at the same time i was very disturbed. i wanted to get up and look at it again but i couldn't move at all, like i was frozen. i sat completely still, sort of confused, watching a helicopter move across the sky in the same directing the thing had left in for several minutes until i could move again. i wrote down what i saw into my phone (which i hadn't used to record the thing like an idiot) and the next day at school i asked my friends if they'd seen it. they hadn't. it wasn't surprising, though, since i had seen it at one in the morning and i have that weird talent for noticing things that no one else does. 
i saw it again the night after, at the same exact time. it appeared in the same way, moved the exact same way, and left the same way. the only difference was that i saw a helicopter beforehand that time. once again, i forgot to record it and nobody else saw it. i stayed up again and again in hopes of seeing and recording it but i never did.

content.detailedDescription:
An aircraft engineer, a pilot and a scientist are together new year's eve ( the three of us don't drink) and the scientist looks up at approx elevation of 70deg and points out a very bright light that stands out from the stars in the north and calls it as a satellite. we all look up, and as we do, the "satellite"  begins moving faster and then stops dead in the sky at relatively 90deg elevation above us but continued to move, stop and flash; which was a continued pattern for approx 1/3 of the sighting. 

we kept watching it, somewhat flabbergasted. we followed it for 23 minutes total as it continued to move at rediculous breakneck speeds, so much so that the light it was emitting was blurred behind it as it went (we did the math at the time and estimated some moves were made at least at mach 3-4 possibly higher!!...But with not a single sound). it remained mostly in a ne bearing as it continued making seemingly impossible stops, right angle turns, arcs, moving in all directions at some point but it was moving in 4 dimensions; in that it was not just moving up, down, left, right; but diagonally also. it would stop, move up (what seemed like) a few hundred meters then move parallel to the line it just made back in the opposite direction! (like playing a game of snake) at times it looked like it was trying to hide amongst stars. the last time we saw it it literally faded away. we continued to look diligently for it but to no avail. 

 it seemed intelligent; playful almost. it was not a plane, as we were near a regional airport and saw a plane pass as we were watching (which gave us a good reference point, but we were all very used to seeing planes land, takeoff and familiar with flight patterns/lights). we saw another plane not long after "it" "left". it was very strange indeed. it is something that has stuck with me and something i will never forget and something iwill forever ponder i guess. what it was doing goes against/defies everything i know of physics. thank you for the opportunity to share my story with a willing ear. kind regards.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: An aircraft engineer, a pilot and a scientist are together and have a very strange encounter with a light moving at rediculous estimated speeds, making impossible stops,turns and  looked like it was trying to hide amongst stars.

content.detailedDescription:
I was on my way to pick up a family member from work at 11:00pm, when i first saw the object.  i noticed it because it was so bright in comparison to the surrounding stars.  with a very bright moon, all other stars were washed out.

when i first spotted it, my first thought was jupiter.  it was soon obvious it wasn't jupiter when it began moving from east to west, towards me.  i got the impression it was descending, but i've no way of verifying that, since the size didn't change appreciably.  

since i was driving, and there was some traffic, i couldn't keep my eyes fixed on it, but when i could, it was very obviously moving across the sky.

when i pulled into the parking lot, i got out and looked for it, it was gone.  so it was either very low, small, and fast; or high and even faster.  i saw no further sign of it after that...

feeling?  rabid curiosity.  i've no idea what it was/is.  don't ask me how i know, but it just didn't seem like an airplane.  there are two airports within the area of walla walla and college place.  walla walla regional airport, and martin field in college place.  in my opinion, there's little chance it was an airplane landing at either.

at my last vision of it, it was headed generally directly west.
content.summary: Very bright object to the left, and below, the moon.  almost directly overhead, and descending.

content.detailedDescription: My friend and i were standing outside and i looked up and saw 2 little lights chasing one another then another one joined them they seemed to be flying back and forth then one would fly behind some trees and the others looked like they were trying to find him then the one behind the trees world pop up really fast and fly around with them. i thought it was cool so i sat outside and watched they looked like they were playing they would hover over the treetops then go straight down. when the 2 went behind the trees out of sight of the one, the one that was left it turned red then when the one behind the trees popped up from behind the trees the one that turned red turned white as soon as it saw his friend. they both headed for the treetops and disappeared like they landed. i thought wow i have to tell someone what i just saw. i didn't have a camera and my friend didn't have one either. i wish i could've taken pictures.
content.summary: At first i thought they were stars until they started moving so looked like stars

content.detailedDescription:
It was a cool dry sunny day.  i was outside on my patio and decided to take a few photos.  i did not hear or see anything a the time.  i reviewed the pics i had just taken when i noticed something in the photos.  i zoomed in and i was shocked and felt overwhelmed at seeing a strange object in the sky.  i looked at the next photo and it was not in the same spot, it had moved very close to my house, which would have taken the object a blink of an eye to get there, because of how i took the photos.  it looked like a spherical shape with the inside middle glowing.  it looked like it was pewter in color.  i showed this pic to a couple of people who were shocked as well.  

*** my phone would not let me attach the photos.  please let me know how to send it differently.  i need to know what that object was.
content.summary: When looking at the photos i had just taken, i noticed something odd.  i had noticed something that looked like a sphere.  it was a pewter color, but seemed to be glowing in the middle.  it made no sound.

content.detailedDescription: Stationed at camp pendleton, my wife and i were watching a video on our back patio on a friday night.  i had dozed off, and my wife woke me up asking what something was. we both observed five slow moving circular lights moving in unison (could not distinguish the outline, but definitely seemed to be a single object) moving east to west (mainland towards ocean).  our appx 8x12 ft patio was surrounded by a five ft wall. by the time we were able to get out of our chairs and exit our patio the lights were gone. the lights had been at a low altitude (appx 500-1000 ft), moving steady but slowly, and noiseless.
content.summary: 5 orbs, slow moving e to w, no sound, low altitude
